<br>
...long after the player who started it deleted the character and apparently no longer has a computer that can play EQ. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
 <br>
Legitimate option? Certainly. One that takes a LOT of serious forethought? Darn tootin. There are certainly races for which slavery IS part of the equation-Teir'dal certainly take slaves,for example. As do humans, Trolls and ogres might-if they didn't eat them most of the time.<br>
<br>
Until the long period of  silence on Atrilinea's player's part pretty much told me that she isn't coming back,I had a good set of armor,weapon,and a horde of Deathfist belts waiting to get her back on her feet(it's since gone to guild newbies instead). Remember,if you DO something like this with someone that they're playing for fun too...act accordingly,and for crying out loud if it isn't obvious-DON'T RP this sort of thing with someone who's emotionally not up to it-like minors. Morgrist would have made a cruel and manipulative master,but the idea is to roleplay,not to make someone's gameplay miserable.<br>
 <br>
-Morgrist Vanadil (League of Shadows)<br>
